                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;This is a pretty limited reinvention of &lt;code&gt;zip&lt;/code&gt; and the wording is rather misleading. If you&apos;re going to reinvent the wheel (don&apos;t--it&apos;s a builtin function, not a dependency), at least &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/a/60842028/6243352&quot;&gt;this answer&lt;/a&gt; accepts a variable number of iterables and generally behaves as you&apos;d expect &lt;code&gt;zip&lt;/code&gt; to.&lt;/span&gt;

