                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment110540746_62479781&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2020-06-22 00:56:59Z, License: CC BY-SA 4.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Jun 22, 2020 at 0:56&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@user2357112supportsMonica Agree. For printing, the iteration performance is determined by the slow system I/O operations, hence is insensitive to the performance of the &lt;code&gt;zip()&lt;/code&gt; function or the other approaches that I have considered.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/5722359/sun-bear&quot; title=&quot;6,638 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Sun Bear&lt;/a&gt;
